casebody.data:
Pietro Antonio MACCHIONE v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 8298. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 14, 1936. Benjamin W. Henderson, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., of Los Angeles, Cal.

Before WILBUR and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issued forthwith.
